1
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:13,840
<i>What's the deal between
Ms. Claire and Mr. Chris?</i>

2
00:00:14,560 --> 00:00:17,599
<i>Why do I have to answer
for something I didn't do?</i>

3
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:18,639
Why did you do this?

4
00:00:18,640 --> 00:00:19,959
Because I wanted you to know

5
00:00:19,960 --> 00:00:22,839
<i>that you can never beat me.</i>

6
00:00:22,840 --> 00:00:24,359
Can we let bygones be bygones?

7
00:00:24,360 --> 00:00:26,599
<i>If you let Claire crawl back into it,</i>

8
00:00:26,600 --> 00:00:27,759
you'll be left with nothing.

9
00:00:27,760 --> 00:00:30,759
I'll never hand over
the company or Chris to her.

10
00:00:30,760 --> 00:00:34,240
If you don't have any plans today,
want to go for a drive with me?

11
00:00:44,280 --> 00:00:45,280
What do you think?

12
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:47,399
It's beautiful.

13
00:00:47,400 --> 00:00:49,160
Why did you bring me here, Grandpa?

14
00:00:49,880 --> 00:00:52,039
Well, take a look around.

15
00:00:52,040 --> 00:00:53,840
Do you recognize anything?

16
00:00:55,440 --> 00:00:56,400
Look.

17
00:00:58,000 --> 00:00:59,079
I don't.

18
00:00:59,080 --> 00:01:01,159
What's so special about this place?

19
00:01:01,160 --> 00:01:03,480
This is a French restaurant.

20
00:01:04,560 --> 00:01:09,400
I thought if I brought you to a place
that used to bring you joy

21
00:01:10,080 --> 00:01:12,839
and served the food you liked,

22
00:01:12,840 --> 00:01:18,440
maybe those old feelings
might bring your memory back.

23
00:01:19,560 --> 00:01:20,400
Claire!

24
00:01:21,800 --> 00:01:23,119
Aunt Rin.

25
00:01:23,120 --> 00:01:25,200
I'm so glad you agreed to come.

26
00:01:26,160 --> 00:01:27,400
She wanted to have a meal with you.

27
00:01:28,280 --> 00:01:29,880
I see. Okay.

28
00:01:30,480 --> 00:01:33,400
We can talk during the meal.

29
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:37,000
I'm sure
you'll start remembering some things.

30
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:39,799
- Come on.
- Then let's go inside.

31
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:41,199
- Let's go.
- Everyone's here.

32
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:42,480
Everyone?

33
00:01:43,160 --> 00:01:45,000
Let's go. Come on.

34
00:01:49,240 --> 00:01:50,280
Cha.

35
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:53,960
Why didn't you tell me
we'd be dining with the chairman?

36
00:01:54,520 --> 00:01:55,920
I could've prepared myself better.

37
00:01:57,600 --> 00:01:58,880
I'm glad I didn't.

38
00:01:59,480 --> 00:02:02,400
So you wouldn't freeze up.
and you could be yourself.

39
00:02:08,639 --> 00:02:10,399
Thank you for giving me a chance, Cha.

40
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:13,920
I promise I will impress the chairman

41
00:02:14,600 --> 00:02:16,760
and convince him to let me marry
someone as great as you.

42
00:02:18,640 --> 00:02:19,920
I'll be watching.

43
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:24,119
Come on in.

44
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:26,080
Come in. Do you recognize anything?

45
00:02:30,720 --> 00:02:32,080
Ms. Claire.

46
00:02:39,560 --> 00:02:40,799
- Hello.
- Hello.

47
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:42,039
I'm Ms. Nalin's relative.

48
00:02:42,040 --> 00:02:43,959
The doctor called to say she got worse.

49
00:02:43,960 --> 00:02:45,400
One moment, please.

50
00:02:48,680 --> 00:02:51,440
Ms. Nalin has been moved to the ICU.

51
00:02:57,160 --> 00:03:00,320
What? The chairman's at Hatchery?

52
00:03:02,040 --> 00:03:03,000
Thanks a lot.

53
00:03:07,160 --> 00:03:08,760
Ms. Claire's favorite restaurant.

54
00:03:16,200 --> 00:03:17,160
Hello?

55
00:03:19,440 --> 00:03:21,759
What is going on, Grandpa?

56
00:03:21,760 --> 00:03:25,080
Well, Cha and Aunt Rin
wanted to have a meal with you.

57
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:28,559
You said you wanted
to clear the air about last night,

58
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:32,280
so I thought a meal would help
resolve our misunderstanding.

59
00:03:33,480 --> 00:03:34,560
When she told me,

60
00:03:35,160 --> 00:03:38,919
I didn't believe you guys
could actually be civil to each other.

61
00:03:38,920 --> 00:03:42,920
So I took this opportunity
to celebrate your return.

62
00:03:45,080 --> 00:03:46,600
Uh, what about Chan?

63
00:03:49,160 --> 00:03:50,480
I didn't tell him.

64
00:03:51,720 --> 00:03:53,920
I asked your grandfather not to tell Chan.

65
00:03:54,600 --> 00:03:59,120
Because if he knew,
he definitely wouldn't let you come out.

66
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:05,160
Don't worry. I've got you.

67
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:07,080
Come on, sit down.

68
00:04:09,640 --> 00:04:10,760
Sit down.

69
00:04:12,720 --> 00:04:15,479
<i>The patient isn't responding
to the platelets we gave them.</i>

70
00:04:15,480 --> 00:04:17,599
Her kidneys
might have stopped functioning,

71
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:19,958
along with other internal organs.

72
00:04:19,959 --> 00:04:24,639
There's a high risk she might
pass away during the surgery.

73
00:04:24,640 --> 00:04:29,039
Another option
is we let the patient's body

74
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:32,040
produce platelets on its own
before operating,

75
00:04:32,640 --> 00:04:35,519
but it's risky
for her body system to fail.

76
00:04:35,520 --> 00:04:38,239
Which option gives
a better chance of survival, Doctor?

77
00:04:38,240 --> 00:04:39,879
Even 1% matters.

78
00:04:39,880 --> 00:04:43,559
I'm ready to choose
the option that can save her.

79
00:04:43,560 --> 00:04:46,440
If that's the case,
I'll review our options.

80
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:49,399
- Thank you.
- Please excuse me.

81
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:50,480
Sure.

82
00:05:00,240 --> 00:05:01,079
What's up, Tun?

83
00:05:01,080 --> 00:05:03,519
The company's PR department
just called me.

84
00:05:03,520 --> 00:05:05,279
They said they couldn't reach you.

85
00:05:05,280 --> 00:05:07,440
Oh, why did they call?

86
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:09,960
It's about Ms. Claire.

87
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:13,440
The reporters found out
she's out of the hospital.

88
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:17,760
How did they find out?

89
00:05:18,520 --> 00:05:21,800
I'm looking into it.
But we have a bigger problem.

90
00:05:22,520 --> 00:05:24,720
Some of the reporters
are on their way to her.

91
00:05:26,760 --> 00:05:27,800
Okay.

92
00:07:08,480 --> 00:07:10,559
I don't usually drink,

93
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:13,319
but since today is a special occasion,

94
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:16,520
I'll treat myself to a glass of wine.

95
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:20,720
Hey.

96
00:07:22,200 --> 00:07:23,640
You know what?

97
00:07:24,560 --> 00:07:26,360
For the past six months,

98
00:07:26,960 --> 00:07:31,080
I prayed to every sacred being
to bring you back to me.

99
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:33,119
And here we are,

100
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:37,000
you're sitting right next to me,
right here, right now.

101
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,280
I have nothing to say

102
00:07:41,080 --> 00:07:42,920
except the fact that...

103
00:07:44,040 --> 00:07:45,560
you're safe now.

104
00:07:49,440 --> 00:07:54,720
Alright, let us all drink
to welcome Claire back home to us.

105
00:08:18,080 --> 00:08:21,040
I'm sorry,
but I've never drunk wine before.

106
00:08:27,920 --> 00:08:32,239
I mean, I think I might have been
in the hospital for a bit too long.

107
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:33,360
I see.

108
00:08:34,679 --> 00:08:35,880
Oh, it's fine.

109
00:08:37,559 --> 00:08:38,919
That might be it.

110
00:08:39,760 --> 00:08:41,880
Then try the soup.

111
00:08:42,559 --> 00:08:44,879
This is your favorite soup.

112
00:08:44,880 --> 00:08:46,880
See if it still tastes the same.

113
00:08:58,680 --> 00:09:01,039
I can't recall the taste.

114
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:02,920
It tastes a bit unusual. What is it?

115
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:05,200
- Uh, it's...
- Chris.

116
00:09:06,440 --> 00:09:10,720
Do you know why I invited you
to join us today?

117
00:09:14,240 --> 00:09:15,399
Cha.

118
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:18,640
Because I wanted you to hear it yourself

119
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:21,880
what Claire told me this morning.

120
00:09:23,040 --> 00:09:25,640
Why don't you say it again
so everyone else can hear?

121
00:09:28,320 --> 00:09:29,600
Cha.

122
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:34,200
I thought we agreed
there'd be no trouble today.

123
00:09:34,800 --> 00:09:36,159
There's no trouble, Dad.

124
00:09:36,160 --> 00:09:39,199
I'm just asking her to say it again.

125
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:40,920
Does it sound like I'm picking a fight?

126
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:48,000
You don't have to if you don't want to.

127
00:09:49,760 --> 00:09:51,039
It's fine.

128
00:09:51,040 --> 00:09:54,520
I just told Cha that
I'd stay away from Chris.

129
00:09:59,480 --> 00:10:00,400
See?

130
00:10:00,920 --> 00:10:05,680
Her saying that means she admits that

131
00:10:06,440 --> 00:10:08,080
she slept with my boyfriend.

132
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:10,319
That's not true, Grandpa.

133
00:10:10,320 --> 00:10:13,119
I said that because
I wanted us to be on good terms.

134
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:15,520
As for other things I did,
I really don't remember.

135
00:10:16,880 --> 00:10:19,040
You don't? But you remember
everything else perfectly.

136
00:10:19,640 --> 00:10:21,680
Cha, that's enough.

137
00:10:22,400 --> 00:10:24,000
Ms. Claire and I never slept together.

138
00:10:24,600 --> 00:10:25,760
You've got it all wrong.

139
00:10:26,840 --> 00:10:28,680
Alright, that's enough.

140
00:10:29,720 --> 00:10:34,599
Didn't I ask you nicely today
to let me celebrate Claire's return?

141
00:10:34,600 --> 00:10:36,840
There will be no more of this talk.

142
00:10:43,040 --> 00:10:44,799
Keep eating, Claire.

143
00:10:44,800 --> 00:10:46,000
Yes.

144
00:11:02,440 --> 00:11:03,919
What soup is this again?

145
00:11:03,920 --> 00:11:05,480
Your favorite one.

146
00:11:07,160 --> 00:11:09,760
It's lobster bisque.

147
00:11:11,760 --> 00:11:12,640
Lobster?

148
00:11:15,320 --> 00:11:16,839
Lobster, the shellfish?

149
00:11:16,840 --> 00:11:19,400
Duh, what else could lobster be?

150
00:11:23,160 --> 00:11:26,240
Well, I need to use restroom.

151
00:11:26,920 --> 00:11:27,840
Wait, Claire.

152
00:11:28,560 --> 00:11:29,800
Is something wrong?

153
00:11:30,920 --> 00:11:33,119
No, please excuse me.

154
00:11:33,120 --> 00:11:36,440
Don't be long. The main course is waiting.

155
00:12:10,960 --> 00:12:15,640
Do you know why I side with Claire in this
even though she's in the wrong?

156
00:12:16,440 --> 00:12:18,079
The other party is just as guilty.

157
00:12:18,080 --> 00:12:22,640
Because that person already
has a partner of their own,

158
00:12:25,080 --> 00:12:27,960
yet they still get involved
with someone else's partner.

159
00:12:35,480 --> 00:12:37,159
Mr. Thiwa! Mr. Thiwa!

160
00:12:37,160 --> 00:12:39,719
- Guys, you can't come in here.
- Please, guys.

161
00:12:39,720 --> 00:12:41,919
Excuse me, sir. We're from the press.

162
00:12:41,920 --> 00:12:43,919
We heard Ms. Claire's out of the hospital.

163
00:12:43,920 --> 00:12:45,159
Is it true, sir?

164
00:12:45,160 --> 00:12:46,999
- The press?
- Is it true, sir?

165
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:48,639
How did they find out about Claire?

166
00:12:48,640 --> 00:12:49,999
- Sir?
- Is it true, sir?

167
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:50,919
No photos, please.

168
00:12:50,920 --> 00:12:52,679
<i>Don't worry, Mom.</i>

169
00:12:52,680 --> 00:12:56,080
<i>I'll never hand over
the company or Chris to her.</i>

170
00:12:56,720 --> 00:12:58,080
But you have to help me.

171
00:12:59,240 --> 00:13:00,840
You have to talk to Dad for me.

172
00:13:01,440 --> 00:13:03,039
What do you want me to tell him?

173
00:13:03,040 --> 00:13:07,680
You have to tell him we want to
throw a welcome party for Claire.

174
00:13:08,680 --> 00:13:09,720
What did you say?

175
00:13:10,600 --> 00:13:12,920
- A welcome party for her?
- Yes.

176
00:13:13,520 --> 00:13:15,039
And not just any party either.

177
00:13:15,040 --> 00:13:17,079
Because I'm going to invite the press

178
00:13:17,080 --> 00:13:20,040
along with an announcement
about her big return.

179
00:13:20,640 --> 00:13:23,080
Sir, is it true?

180
00:13:24,880 --> 00:13:25,719
Is it true, sir?

181
00:13:25,720 --> 00:13:27,639
- Is it true, sir?
- Is it true, sir?

182
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:28,920
Don't worry, honey.

183
00:13:29,720 --> 00:13:31,200
Let Cha handle this.

184
00:13:33,520 --> 00:13:35,399
- You got it.
- Please answer, sir.

185
00:13:35,400 --> 00:13:36,439
Sir?

186
00:13:36,440 --> 00:13:38,999
- Is it true, sir?
- Is it true, sir?

187
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:42,199
- Sir, please answer.
- Guys, how about this?

188
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:44,879
I'll answer all your questions.

189
00:13:44,880 --> 00:13:46,399
Let's go that way, guys.

190
00:13:46,400 --> 00:13:47,400
<i>Are you crazy?</i>

191
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:50,159
The 60th anniversary is coming up.

192
00:13:50,160 --> 00:13:52,799
Instead of making her
stay as quiet as possible,

193
00:13:52,800 --> 00:13:54,839
you're putting her in the spotlight.

194
00:13:54,840 --> 00:13:58,439
What if it gives your father the idea
to make her chairman at the event?

195
00:13:58,440 --> 00:14:00,840
And what if people find out
she has amnesia?

196
00:14:02,680 --> 00:14:04,119
Haven't you noticed?

197
00:14:04,120 --> 00:14:08,039
Since Claire got back, Chan hasn't
let her step foot into the company.

198
00:14:08,040 --> 00:14:09,279
Do you know why?

199
00:14:09,280 --> 00:14:11,680
Because he's afraid
people will find out the truth.

200
00:14:12,280 --> 00:14:14,559
If everyone knows she has amnesia,

201
00:14:14,560 --> 00:14:17,119
do you think Dad would make her chairman?

202
00:14:17,120 --> 00:14:20,960
Not to mention the other shareholders.
They would never agree.

203
00:14:22,600 --> 00:14:26,039
So, all we need to do right now is

204
00:14:26,040 --> 00:14:29,560
let everyone know Claire
is just a dumb woman with amnesia.

205
00:14:37,680 --> 00:14:38,519
Go ahead, guys.

206
00:14:38,520 --> 00:14:41,119
There are rumors
Ms. Claire's out of the hospital.

207
00:14:41,120 --> 00:14:42,239
Is it true?

208
00:14:42,240 --> 00:14:46,799
You guys are real professionals,
so fast with your info. Yes, it's true.

209
00:14:46,800 --> 00:14:49,280
- Whoa.
- It's true.

210
00:14:52,840 --> 00:14:55,959
Then why hasn't there been
any news or updates about Ms. Claire?

211
00:14:55,960 --> 00:14:58,160
Uh, is there some kind of secret?

212
00:14:58,800 --> 00:14:59,879
Yes, is there a secret?

213
00:14:59,880 --> 00:15:03,319
We didn't actually mean
to keep this a secret.

214
00:15:03,320 --> 00:15:06,080
But the Claire that you guys will see...

215
00:15:07,520 --> 00:15:08,640
is different.

216
00:15:09,240 --> 00:15:11,720
- What do you mean by "different"?
- I don't get it.

217
00:15:30,640 --> 00:15:33,120
Claire. Claire.

218
00:15:34,840 --> 00:15:38,280
Claire. Stop avoiding me, Claire.

219
00:15:39,440 --> 00:15:40,440
I'm sorry.

220
00:15:40,960 --> 00:15:43,960
Did you really tell Cha that, Claire?

221
00:15:44,680 --> 00:15:46,360
Are you really done with me?

222
00:15:46,960 --> 00:15:48,479
But I love you, Claire.

223
00:15:48,480 --> 00:15:50,119
I'm pretending to love Cha

224
00:15:50,120 --> 00:15:51,720
because I don't want
to get you in trouble.

225
00:15:52,800 --> 00:15:54,720
I'm not breaking up with you.

226
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:56,920
Honey.

227
00:15:59,320 --> 00:16:00,600
Please don't go.

228
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:04,680
I'm not breaking up with you, Claire.

229
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:12,320
You bastard!

230
00:16:17,920 --> 00:16:20,719
What do you mean by "different"?

231
00:16:20,720 --> 00:16:22,160
Well, her mental state...

232
00:16:22,760 --> 00:16:25,239
Ah, that's not accurate.

233
00:16:25,240 --> 00:16:28,480
It's... her brain, actually.

234
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:31,239
But I don't want to say too much.

235
00:16:31,240 --> 00:16:33,759
Let's just say if you guys
really want to know,

236
00:16:33,760 --> 00:16:36,359
Ms. Claire is in the restroom.
You should ask her yourself.

237
00:16:36,360 --> 00:16:38,159
Oh, Ms. Claire is here too?

238
00:16:38,160 --> 00:16:41,599
- Shall we go?
- Yes, let's go.

239
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:42,720
Let's go.

240
00:16:44,120 --> 00:16:45,120
- You.
- What?

241
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:48,800
Are you mad? It's me who should be mad.

242
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:50,720
Claire is my fiancée.

243
00:16:53,400 --> 00:16:54,640
So what if she is?

244
00:16:55,880 --> 00:16:57,240
Claire doesn't love you anymore.

245
00:16:57,840 --> 00:17:00,360
You're just a puppet for the public.

246
00:17:09,800 --> 00:17:10,880
So what did they want?

247
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:16,118
They wanted to know about Claire, Dad.

248
00:17:16,119 --> 00:17:17,919
But I didn't tell them anything.

249
00:17:17,920 --> 00:17:20,160
I told them to ask Claire themselves.

250
00:17:31,240 --> 00:17:32,919
I'm really curious to see

251
00:17:32,920 --> 00:17:37,760
what will happen if news breaks out
that the highly-capable socialite Claire

252
00:17:38,760 --> 00:17:39,800
has amnesia.

253
00:17:44,520 --> 00:17:47,519
- Over there! Guys, come on!
- Hurry!

254
00:17:47,520 --> 00:17:49,680
Ms. Claire! Ms. Claire!

255
00:17:50,400 --> 00:17:52,439
- Ms. Claire?
- No photos, please.

256
00:17:52,440 --> 00:17:54,000
- Ms. Claire!
- No photos, please.

257
00:17:55,320 --> 00:17:56,360
Ms. Claire?

258
00:17:57,040 --> 00:17:58,239
Chris.

259
00:17:58,240 --> 00:17:59,719
Hey.

260
00:17:59,720 --> 00:18:02,320
What's going on here? Did you two fight?

261
00:18:03,640 --> 00:18:06,600
I think you should ask him
what he tried to do to Claire.

262
00:18:08,160 --> 00:18:09,920
I didn't do anything, Cha.

263
00:18:10,680 --> 00:18:13,359
Ms. Claire, are you okay?

264
00:18:13,360 --> 00:18:15,760
Please, guys.
She's not ready to talk to you.

265
00:18:17,240 --> 00:18:19,039
- Just...
- Just one question, please.

266
00:18:19,040 --> 00:18:20,240
What's wrong with you?

267
00:18:21,560 --> 00:18:23,400
- Shellfish.
- What?

268
00:18:24,880 --> 00:18:26,639
I'm allergic to shellfish.

269
00:18:26,640 --> 00:18:27,720
Hey.

270
00:18:28,880 --> 00:18:30,000
Come again?

271
00:18:37,040 --> 00:18:39,639
- Claire. Claire!
- Hey, she fainted!

272
00:18:39,640 --> 00:18:41,919
Hey!

273
00:18:41,920 --> 00:18:42,999
Hey.

274
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:45,879
- Get out!
- Hey. Hey. Hey.

275
00:18:45,880 --> 00:18:48,079
- Just one more photo.
- Hey. Hey.

276
00:18:48,080 --> 00:18:49,160
Claire?

277
00:18:51,640 --> 00:18:54,600
- Ms. Claire!
- Hey. Hey.

278
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:09,800
INTRARAT HOSPITAL

279
00:19:17,720 --> 00:19:19,920
- Are you with Ms. Claire?
- Oh, yes, I am.

280
00:19:20,600 --> 00:19:21,559
Sir.

281
00:19:21,560 --> 00:19:23,840
Is her condition serious, Doctor?

282
00:19:24,840 --> 00:19:28,600
She had a severe allergic reaction
called systemic anaphylaxis.

283
00:19:29,280 --> 00:19:30,759
It's a medical emergency.

284
00:19:30,760 --> 00:19:33,640
Do you happen to know
what she's allergic to?

285
00:19:36,400 --> 00:19:38,400
- Shellfish.
- What?

286
00:19:39,600 --> 00:19:41,400
I'm allergic to shellfish.

287
00:19:44,120 --> 00:19:45,440
It's shellfish.

288
00:19:46,960 --> 00:19:48,080
I think it's shellfish.

289
00:19:50,320 --> 00:19:52,719
And how is she doing right now?

290
00:19:52,720 --> 00:19:55,680
She's not out of the woods yet.

291
00:19:57,760 --> 00:19:58,960
Sir.

292
00:20:01,440 --> 00:20:02,760
Doctor, uh...

293
00:20:03,400 --> 00:20:05,439
My granddaughter
is going to be okay, right?

294
00:20:05,440 --> 00:20:06,759
Don't worry.

295
00:20:06,760 --> 00:20:09,680
We are doing everything we can
to save her.

296
00:20:10,280 --> 00:20:11,559
Please excuse me.

297
00:20:11,560 --> 00:20:13,119
Please take care of her.

298
00:20:13,120 --> 00:20:14,680
- Thank you, Doctor.
- Sure.

299
00:20:16,200 --> 00:20:17,520
Please sit down, sir.

300
00:20:35,600 --> 00:20:38,400
CHRIS

301
00:20:49,800 --> 00:20:52,520
Do you think Chris did something
to Claire like Chan said?

302
00:20:53,960 --> 00:20:55,879
I don't know.

303
00:20:55,880 --> 00:20:58,240
And I'm not in the listening mood
right now.

304
00:20:58,840 --> 00:21:01,079
I'll just check the CCTV footage.

305
00:21:01,080 --> 00:21:03,680
Then I'll know if they did
anything behind my back.

306
00:21:05,400 --> 00:21:08,040
What about you?
Did you speak with the hospital?

307
00:21:08,640 --> 00:21:10,880
Claire was just putting on an act, right?

308
00:21:11,840 --> 00:21:16,039
No. I talked to the doctor treating her.

309
00:21:16,040 --> 00:21:18,560
She really had a severe
allergic reaction to shellfish.

310
00:21:20,560 --> 00:21:21,959
Allergic to shellfish?

311
00:21:21,960 --> 00:21:23,120
Yes.

312
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:25,120
Are you sure?

313
00:21:26,360 --> 00:21:29,480
Why? You think she was lying?

314
00:21:30,640 --> 00:21:32,920
Has she ever had a shellfish allergy, Mom?

315
00:22:05,880 --> 00:22:07,240
<i>Claire doesn't love you anymore.</i>

316
00:22:08,280 --> 00:22:11,240
You're just a puppet for the public.

317
00:22:21,560 --> 00:22:24,040
<i>Where are you? I'm downstairs.</i>

318
00:22:37,720 --> 00:22:38,720
Who are you?

319
00:22:41,800 --> 00:22:44,480
You're new here,
so you probably don't know me.

320
00:22:46,920 --> 00:22:48,280
I'm Nitchan.

321
00:22:49,240 --> 00:22:51,160
I'm the Head of Strategy at TGL.

322
00:22:51,760 --> 00:22:54,119
Besides being the Head of Strategy,

323
00:22:54,120 --> 00:22:56,400
I'm also Claire's fiancé.

324
00:22:57,880 --> 00:22:59,320
Stay away from her

325
00:22:59,960 --> 00:23:02,000
if you don't want
a repeat of today's mess.

326
00:23:05,800 --> 00:23:09,040
You should tell that to her,
because she's the one who approached me.

327
00:23:10,040 --> 00:23:13,120
Do you think
you're the first guy she's done this to?

328
00:23:13,720 --> 00:23:14,879
You don't believe me?

329
00:23:14,880 --> 00:23:17,359
Then you can wait and see.

330
00:23:17,360 --> 00:23:19,039
You'll see that she doesn't view you

331
00:23:19,040 --> 00:23:22,280
as anything more than a tool
to beat Ms. Cha.

332
00:23:29,400 --> 00:23:30,920
<i>Did you send for me?</i>

333
00:23:41,120 --> 00:23:42,560
What did you say to Chris?

334
00:23:44,920 --> 00:23:46,120
Why?

335
00:23:46,960 --> 00:23:49,360
Did that guy break up with you, huh?

336
00:23:49,880 --> 00:23:53,719
I told you before,
stay out of my business.

337
00:23:53,720 --> 00:23:58,000
If you don't listen,
you know what I'm capable of.

338
00:23:59,440 --> 00:24:01,880
But your business is my business too.

339
00:24:02,600 --> 00:24:05,239
You're so blinded
by your need to beat those two

340
00:24:05,240 --> 00:24:08,120
that you forgot
you're the Vice Chairman of TGL,

341
00:24:08,960 --> 00:24:10,519
the chairman's granddaughter,

342
00:24:10,520 --> 00:24:13,080
and my fiancée.

343
00:24:13,800 --> 00:24:17,120
So what? Are you humiliated?

344
00:24:21,840 --> 00:24:24,080
<i>How many more men
do you need to be satisfied?</i>

345
00:24:24,840 --> 00:24:26,040
You can't handle it?

346
00:24:26,640 --> 00:24:28,240
What do you want to do to me?

347
00:24:32,520 --> 00:24:33,640
Go ahead.

348
00:24:34,840 --> 00:24:35,760
Choke me.

349
00:24:36,640 --> 00:24:38,600
You want me dead anyway, right?

350
00:24:39,520 --> 00:24:41,119
Choke me.

351
00:24:41,120 --> 00:24:42,560
I said choke me!

352
00:25:39,160 --> 00:25:40,160
Tun.

353
00:25:42,640 --> 00:25:45,560
The chairman made it home safely, right?

354
00:25:46,600 --> 00:25:47,640
Yes, he did.

355
00:25:48,520 --> 00:25:52,920
She's safe now, right?
She's lucky you got her here in time.

356
00:25:57,280 --> 00:25:59,560
Actually, she's lucky
she was conscious enough

357
00:26:00,480 --> 00:26:03,760
to tell me about her allergy,
so they treated her in time.

358
00:26:04,640 --> 00:26:08,199
Do you think the chairman
will suspect anything?

359
00:26:08,200 --> 00:26:10,520
About her sudden shellfish allergy?

360
00:26:12,040 --> 00:26:13,559
I don't think so.

361
00:26:13,560 --> 00:26:17,599
Right now, he's shocked
and worried about Claire.

362
00:26:17,600 --> 00:26:19,400
He wouldn't get suspicious.

363
00:26:20,520 --> 00:26:25,960
But if Ms. Rossarin and Ms. Cha
get suspicious, they won't let it slide.

364
00:26:29,040 --> 00:26:32,000
Right now, we need to figure out
how to explain her allergy.

365
00:26:34,520 --> 00:26:36,800
Someone tipped off the reporters, right?

366
00:26:37,640 --> 00:26:40,199
Yes. I asked around.

367
00:26:40,200 --> 00:26:44,120
They said our PR department
contacted them to report on Ms. Claire.

368
00:26:45,920 --> 00:26:48,400
I think you can guess who it was.

369
00:26:53,520 --> 00:26:57,400
Ms. Cha probably wants to show that
even if Claire is fine,

370
00:26:58,040 --> 00:26:59,920
she's still unfit to run the company.

371
00:27:02,120 --> 00:27:03,320
Are you saying...

372
00:27:04,640 --> 00:27:07,480
Ms. Cha is after Ms. Claire's position?

373
00:27:22,320 --> 00:27:23,320
No.

374
00:27:25,240 --> 00:27:27,320
She's after the chairman's position.

375
00:27:29,720 --> 00:27:33,160
Before this, she thought we were
lying about Ms. Claire being alive,

376
00:27:34,080 --> 00:27:35,959
so she didn't do anything.

377
00:27:35,960 --> 00:27:40,280
Because in the end,
the chairmanship would be hers anyway.

378
00:27:41,840 --> 00:27:43,880
But the moment we brought Claire back,

379
00:27:45,400 --> 00:27:46,880
she's got to do everything in her power

380
00:27:47,960 --> 00:27:50,320
to stop Claire from getting that seat.

381
00:27:52,720 --> 00:27:54,840
We can't tell the chairman
about this either.

382
00:27:55,600 --> 00:27:57,040
It'll stress him out too much.

383
00:28:06,440 --> 00:28:10,280
The only person who can stop them is her.

384
00:28:14,440 --> 00:28:16,759
What? The camera is broken?

385
00:28:16,760 --> 00:28:19,039
Yes, I'm really sorry about that.

386
00:28:19,040 --> 00:28:22,480
Hey, is it really broken,
or are you just holding out on me?

387
00:28:23,240 --> 00:28:25,759
I get that it's a high-end hotel,

388
00:28:25,760 --> 00:28:28,919
and requesting CCTV footage
requires going through hoops.

389
00:28:28,920 --> 00:28:31,879
But you're taking the easy way out
by telling me it's broken?

390
00:28:31,880 --> 00:28:34,839
No, ma'am. That camera is really broken.

391
00:28:34,840 --> 00:28:36,559
It's been down for just three days.

392
00:28:36,560 --> 00:28:39,839
<i>But if you don't believe me,
you can come take a look.</i>

393
00:28:39,840 --> 00:28:43,280
Though you may
need to show a police report.

394
00:28:43,880 --> 00:28:45,840
I don't have time for that.

395
00:28:51,880 --> 00:28:53,080
All done, sir.

396
00:29:05,600 --> 00:29:06,640
Thank you.

397
00:29:09,760 --> 00:29:10,800
Please excuse me.

398
00:29:29,720 --> 00:29:32,880
Cha. Are you still mad at me?

399
00:29:33,640 --> 00:29:37,320
I told you, I didn't do anything.
I just went to the restroom.

400
00:29:38,120 --> 00:29:41,600
Didn't do anything?
Then why did Chan punch you?

401
00:29:42,680 --> 00:29:44,439
Because he was crazy, Cha.

402
00:29:44,440 --> 00:29:47,559
<i>He wanted everyone to see
that he's Ms. Claire's fiancé</i>

403
00:29:47,560 --> 00:29:49,679
<i>and he can do whatever he wants.</i>

404
00:29:49,680 --> 00:29:52,159
<i>Since this evening,</i>

405
00:29:52,160 --> 00:29:55,559
<i>you haven't asked a single thing
that shows you care about me.</i>

406
00:29:55,560 --> 00:29:59,839
<i>You just keep asking about what Chan said.</i>

407
00:29:59,840 --> 00:30:03,879
Hey. You believe Chan over me now,
don't you?

408
00:30:03,880 --> 00:30:05,560
I have to go.

409
00:30:06,400 --> 00:30:09,840
Cha. Tell me you're not mad at me anymore.

410
00:30:10,880 --> 00:30:14,760
You know what will happen
if you cheat on me again, right?

411
00:30:46,120 --> 00:30:49,200
Have someone get the car ready.
I'm going to visit Claire.

412
00:30:50,400 --> 00:30:51,360
Is something wrong?

413
00:30:53,520 --> 00:30:55,679
Dad feels guilty

414
00:30:55,680 --> 00:30:57,639
for taking Claire to that restaurant.

415
00:30:57,640 --> 00:31:00,799
Luckily he ordered
the lobster soup himself.

416
00:31:00,800 --> 00:31:03,560
Otherwise,
he'd think either you or I did it.

417
00:31:06,440 --> 00:31:08,759
Cha, don't talk like that.

418
00:31:08,760 --> 00:31:12,639
Who could have known Claire
would suddenly be allergic to lobster?

419
00:31:12,640 --> 00:31:15,519
She'd never had a problem with it before.

420
00:31:15,520 --> 00:31:19,600
I'm just speaking the truth. Right, Dad?

421
00:31:20,280 --> 00:31:21,640
I suppose.

422
00:31:22,800 --> 00:31:25,840
Even if you didn't cause
her allergic reaction,

423
00:31:27,840 --> 00:31:29,200
those reporters...

424
00:31:29,800 --> 00:31:32,799
How did they know where we were eating?

425
00:31:32,800 --> 00:31:37,680
It could have been a staff member
or someone who saw us and tipped them off.

426
00:31:40,400 --> 00:31:41,600
I asked Chan about that.

427
00:31:43,080 --> 00:31:46,360
He said someone told the press
to report on Claire at the hotel.

428
00:31:47,600 --> 00:31:51,400
So you think I did it, right, Dad?

429
00:31:52,120 --> 00:31:54,959
It's strange. Are Chan and Claire
the only ones living here?

430
00:31:54,960 --> 00:31:56,920
Why do you only believe those two?

431
00:31:58,600 --> 00:32:00,240
I don't just believe Chan.

432
00:32:01,480 --> 00:32:03,120
I believe what I see too.

433
00:32:04,480 --> 00:32:07,519
And you've constantly shown me
what kind of person you are!

434
00:32:07,520 --> 00:32:08,959
What kind of person am I?

435
00:32:08,960 --> 00:32:11,479
Am I a bad person? Am I evil?

436
00:32:11,480 --> 00:32:13,279
Just you watch, Dad.

437
00:32:13,280 --> 00:32:17,120
I will be the one
who will keep your TGL running.

438
00:32:18,960 --> 00:32:21,120
So you can stop thinking that way.

439
00:32:22,680 --> 00:32:27,360
I will never let you take over my company!

440
00:32:33,000 --> 00:32:35,239
Then who do you have in mind?

441
00:32:35,240 --> 00:32:37,239
Don't tell me you're letting an amnesiac

442
00:32:37,240 --> 00:32:40,520
who doesn't even know
what she's allergic to take over.

443
00:32:41,760 --> 00:32:44,720
Are you sure you can handle my answer?

444
00:32:50,400 --> 00:32:52,000
Wait, Cha!

445
00:32:55,400 --> 00:32:57,920
You've never treated both of us right.

446
00:33:00,040 --> 00:33:02,800
Is it because
Cha isn't your biological daughter?

447
00:33:06,000 --> 00:33:08,240
Can I have my coffee now?

448
00:33:21,560 --> 00:33:25,920
<i>I will never let you take over my company!</i>

449
00:33:27,880 --> 00:33:29,800
Hey, what the hell are you doing?

450
00:33:30,440 --> 00:33:31,479
Give it here.

451
00:33:31,480 --> 00:33:35,759
Why? Since Dad hates me anyway,
he won't mind me doing this.

452
00:33:35,760 --> 00:33:37,839
- Come here.
- Ow!

453
00:33:37,840 --> 00:33:39,679
- Let go. Where are you going?
- Come here.

454
00:33:39,680 --> 00:33:41,200
Let go! Mom!

455
00:33:41,720 --> 00:33:42,920
- Ow!
- Get in here.

456
00:33:44,760 --> 00:33:46,640
Why do you keep making things worse?

457
00:33:47,240 --> 00:33:50,720
Worse? Would me playing nice really help?

458
00:33:51,840 --> 00:33:53,999
Dad doesn't like me anyway.

459
00:33:54,000 --> 00:33:57,720
It was your fault for falling into
Claire's trap from the start.

460
00:33:59,240 --> 00:34:00,120
<i>What's going on?</i>

461
00:34:00,960 --> 00:34:03,039
- Why did you ask me to wear white?
- Hello.

462
00:34:03,040 --> 00:34:04,600
Come, let's sit down.

463
00:34:07,360 --> 00:34:12,159
Please, have a seat. Well,
we are going to register our marriage.

464
00:34:15,000 --> 00:34:17,000
- Come.
- Congratulations, Mom.

465
00:34:20,800 --> 00:34:22,280
What is this, honey?

466
00:34:23,360 --> 00:34:25,639
Cha, what is this?

467
00:34:26,320 --> 00:34:29,760
I have nothing to do with this.
You'll have to ask Dad yourself.

468
00:34:32,000 --> 00:34:33,319
Honey.

469
00:34:33,320 --> 00:34:35,600
You two have looked after me for so long.

470
00:34:36,320 --> 00:34:39,639
I just wanted to show you
that I truly love you.

471
00:34:40,760 --> 00:34:42,198
If you're ready, please sign.

472
00:34:42,199 --> 00:34:43,320
Alright.

473
00:34:44,840 --> 00:34:48,079
MARRIAGE CERTIFICATE

474
00:34:48,080 --> 00:34:49,760
- Right here?
- Yes.

475
00:34:51,280 --> 00:34:52,799
No wonder.

476
00:34:52,800 --> 00:34:55,440
So this is why you all
wanted me to go to Italy.

477
00:35:00,360 --> 00:35:04,799
Turns out you dirty rats
were planning to strike it rich all along.

478
00:35:04,800 --> 00:35:08,800
I'm glad you're here.
Come congratulate me. Come.

479
00:35:09,680 --> 00:35:11,439
Congratulate?

480
00:35:11,440 --> 00:35:14,920
Do you really think
I'll let you marry this woman?

481
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:22,240
You can leave.
There will be no marriage registration.

482
00:35:23,040 --> 00:35:26,520
Or you can stay if you want.
You can be a witness if there's a murder.

483
00:35:27,320 --> 00:35:29,439
I think it's best if I leave.

484
00:35:29,440 --> 00:35:32,240
Once you've settled this,
contact the district office.

485
00:35:33,360 --> 00:35:34,400
Claire.

486
00:35:35,760 --> 00:35:39,599
My mom and dad love each other.
What's your problem?

487
00:35:39,600 --> 00:35:43,400
They haven't even registered,
and you're already calling him "Dad"?

488
00:35:44,120 --> 00:35:47,040
- You're evil.
- What did you say?

489
00:35:47,680 --> 00:35:48,760
Stop it, Cha.

490
00:35:52,480 --> 00:35:53,600
Let me handle this.

491
00:35:56,920 --> 00:35:58,000
Claire.

492
00:35:59,000 --> 00:36:00,320
I know that

493
00:36:01,000 --> 00:36:04,280
you think I'm marrying
your grandfather for his money.

494
00:36:05,280 --> 00:36:07,080
But I truly love Mr. Thiwa.

495
00:36:07,800 --> 00:36:09,040
I don't believe you.

496
00:36:12,920 --> 00:36:15,320
Then what do I have to do?

497
00:36:15,960 --> 00:36:17,159
Just tell me.

498
00:36:17,160 --> 00:36:20,639
I'm ready to prove to you

499
00:36:20,640 --> 00:36:22,720
that I really love Mr. Thiwa.

500
00:36:23,520 --> 00:36:24,480
Can you prove it?

501
00:36:28,720 --> 00:36:30,440
How would you do that?

502
00:36:32,720 --> 00:36:34,199
I know.

503
00:36:34,200 --> 00:36:37,280
Why don't you have a baby with him?

504
00:36:39,520 --> 00:36:41,559
Oh, wait, that won't work.

505
00:36:41,560 --> 00:36:44,599
What if you sleep around,
get pregnant, and claim it's his?

506
00:36:44,600 --> 00:36:46,319
No, that plays right into your hands.

507
00:36:46,320 --> 00:36:47,840
What exactly do you want?

508
00:36:49,080 --> 00:36:50,799
Why are you mocking her like this?

509
00:36:50,800 --> 00:36:53,079
Calm down, Grandpa.

510
00:36:53,080 --> 00:36:55,879
If she wants to prove
she really loves you, it's simple.

511
00:36:55,880 --> 00:36:58,559
Just don't register the marriage.
That's all.

512
00:36:58,560 --> 00:37:03,559
Aunt Rin didn't force me to register.
I was the one who wanted to do it.

513
00:37:03,560 --> 00:37:05,239
See?

514
00:37:05,240 --> 00:37:07,119
The marriage registration

515
00:37:07,120 --> 00:37:10,279
proves your grandfather
really loves my mother,

516
00:37:10,280 --> 00:37:11,879
Then let's flip it.

517
00:37:11,880 --> 00:37:15,559
He doesn't need to register this marriage
to prove his love for you.

518
00:37:15,560 --> 00:37:19,199
Instead, you need to prove to him

519
00:37:19,200 --> 00:37:22,999
that you're marrying him out of pure love,

520
00:37:23,000 --> 00:37:24,880
not for his money.

521
00:37:35,920 --> 00:37:37,879
If you had registered the marriage,

522
00:37:37,880 --> 00:37:39,959
everything would be ours by now.

523
00:37:39,960 --> 00:37:42,600
Hey, are you saying this is my fault?

524
00:37:43,400 --> 00:37:46,119
Do you think if I hadn't made that choice,

525
00:37:46,120 --> 00:37:48,640
you and I would even be
living in this house right now?

526
00:37:53,240 --> 00:37:54,720
Then it's time.

527
00:37:55,920 --> 00:37:57,200
Time for what?

528
00:37:58,240 --> 00:38:00,760
Time for us to take matters
into our own hands.

529
00:38:04,000 --> 00:38:09,080
Since Dad isn't giving us anything anyway,
we have to take it ourselves.

530
00:38:11,800 --> 00:38:12,960
What are you going to do?

531
00:38:16,880 --> 00:38:20,119
Hello? Ms. Nalin?

532
00:38:20,120 --> 00:38:23,240
Oh, yes. How is she doing?

533
00:38:26,000 --> 00:38:28,840
Really? I'll be right over.

534
00:38:30,040 --> 00:38:32,720
What's going on, Chan?
Is her aunt doing okay?

535
00:38:34,080 --> 00:38:35,560
Her aunt woke up.

536
00:38:36,400 --> 00:38:38,600
And she's going to bring her niece back.

537
00:38:55,880 --> 00:38:58,999
Jinla. Can you hear me?

538
00:38:59,000 --> 00:39:00,319
- <i>I can hear you...</i>
- Jinla.

539
00:39:00,320 --> 00:39:02,920
<i>- ...but I can't open my eyes.</i>
- Jinla.

540
00:39:04,280 --> 00:39:06,080
I know you can hear me.

541
00:39:07,480 --> 00:39:08,480
Jinla.

542
00:39:09,800 --> 00:39:14,400
If you knew who I brought with me,
you'd be so happy.

543
00:39:15,000 --> 00:39:17,480
<i>Who? Who even knows me?</i>

544
00:39:26,760 --> 00:39:30,120
Is the one lying there my niece, Jinla?

545
00:39:30,800 --> 00:39:32,319
- Yes, it is.
- <i>That's my aunt's voice.</i>

546
00:39:32,320 --> 00:39:34,360
<i>- You're awake?</i>
- She's been waiting for you.

547
00:39:35,040 --> 00:39:36,480
Go on over to her.

548
00:39:38,000 --> 00:39:39,040
Jin.

549
00:39:40,320 --> 00:39:42,840
<i>Aunt. It's really you.</i>

550
00:39:43,520 --> 00:39:45,040
<i>Aunt, it's me.</i>

551
00:39:47,120 --> 00:39:48,240
Who is this?

552
00:39:50,520 --> 00:39:51,720
This isn't my niece.

553
00:39:53,200 --> 00:39:55,919
- <i>Aunt, it's me, Jin.</i>
- She really is your niece, Jinla.

554
00:39:55,920 --> 00:39:59,520
<i>- Mr. Chan, will you explain it to her?</i>
- But we made her look like this.

555
00:40:00,440 --> 00:40:02,719
It's not true. I don't believe you.

556
00:40:02,720 --> 00:40:05,159
She is not my niece. She is not my niece

557
00:40:05,160 --> 00:40:07,319
I don't believe you. I'm leaving.

558
00:40:07,320 --> 00:40:10,039
Wait, ma'am.
This really is your niece, Jinla.

559
00:40:10,040 --> 00:40:11,079
- She's not.
- Ma'am.

560
00:40:11,080 --> 00:40:12,439
- She's not my niece. No.
- Ma'am.

561
00:40:12,440 --> 00:40:13,480
- Ma'am!
- Ma'am!

562
00:40:14,920 --> 00:40:16,000
Tun, follow her.

563
00:40:16,640 --> 00:40:18,079
- Ma'am!
- <i>No, no!</i>

564
00:40:18,080 --> 00:40:20,439
- Ma'am, wait!
<i>- Aunt, don't go!</i>

565
00:40:20,440 --> 00:40:23,520
<i>Aunt, don't leave, please! Aunt!</i>

566
00:40:25,040 --> 00:40:26,120
Aunt!

567
00:40:30,640 --> 00:40:31,760
You're back.

568
00:40:32,600 --> 00:40:33,640
Hey.

569
00:40:39,680 --> 00:40:40,680
Hey.

570
00:40:42,480 --> 00:40:43,520
Hey.

571
00:40:45,400 --> 00:40:46,480
How are you feeling?

572
00:40:59,560 --> 00:41:01,400
Am I in a hospital?

573
00:41:03,080 --> 00:41:04,520
You were out for a night.

574
00:41:05,680 --> 00:41:07,320
How are you feeling right now?

575
00:41:11,600 --> 00:41:12,600
Well...

576
00:41:13,320 --> 00:41:17,240
I still have a headache,
and my stomach hurts a bit.

577
00:41:22,240 --> 00:41:23,960
I'm allergic to shellfish.

578
00:41:24,600 --> 00:41:25,720
Come again?

579
00:41:28,960 --> 00:41:31,560
- Claire. Claire!
- Hey, she fainted!

580
00:41:34,960 --> 00:41:36,360
Thank you.

581
00:41:39,000 --> 00:41:40,600
Thank you for saving me.

582
00:41:43,200 --> 00:41:45,720
Is there anything else
you haven't told me?

583
00:41:47,640 --> 00:41:48,840
Like what?

584
00:41:52,480 --> 00:41:54,360
When I decided to turn you into Claire,

585
00:41:54,960 --> 00:41:57,519
I had to dig up everything about you.

586
00:41:57,520 --> 00:41:59,880
Why did you leave out
something this important?

587
00:42:01,800 --> 00:42:02,880
Hey.

588
00:42:07,920 --> 00:42:09,520
You mean my shellfish allergy?

589
00:42:13,560 --> 00:42:15,959
I ate it when I was a kid and I...

590
00:42:15,960 --> 00:42:17,879
I almost died from it.

591
00:42:17,880 --> 00:42:20,480
My aunt never let me eat shellfish again.

592
00:42:22,600 --> 00:42:25,279
Then while you're recovering here,

593
00:42:25,280 --> 00:42:27,920
use this time to think things over.

594
00:42:28,520 --> 00:42:30,840
See if there's anything else
you haven't told me.

595
00:42:37,040 --> 00:42:38,960
And you didn't have to thank me.

596
00:42:40,520 --> 00:42:42,000
I can't let you die yet.

597
00:42:46,000 --> 00:42:47,800
Is that all I'm worth to you?

598
00:43:05,320 --> 00:43:06,400
Chan.

599
00:43:07,640 --> 00:43:09,399
Oh, you're awake?

600
00:43:09,400 --> 00:43:10,919
How are you feeling?

601
00:43:10,920 --> 00:43:12,200
What do you want?

602
00:43:13,680 --> 00:43:16,440
The office called
with some questions about work.

603
00:43:52,000 --> 00:43:53,040
Take a look.

604
00:43:56,640 --> 00:44:00,280
SOCIALITE CLAIRE SURVIVED...
BUT LOST HER MEMORY.

605
00:44:08,400 --> 00:44:09,639
What on earth is this?

606
00:44:09,640 --> 00:44:11,280
Who leaked this?

607
00:44:12,480 --> 00:44:14,840
Tun, call a PR meeting right now.

608
00:44:15,360 --> 00:44:17,919
I already had them handle some of it

609
00:44:17,920 --> 00:44:20,560
because you have
a bigger problem to deal with.

610
00:44:22,280 --> 00:44:26,360
I've been told Ms. Cha suddenly
called an executive board meeting.

611
00:44:27,200 --> 00:44:28,120
For what?

612
00:44:29,360 --> 00:44:30,560
Nobody knows.

613
00:44:31,360 --> 00:44:35,840
But I think it has something to do
with the news about Ms. Claire.

614
00:44:49,600 --> 00:44:52,879
You know, when I heard that
Ms. Claire wasn't dead,

615
00:44:52,880 --> 00:44:55,799
my knees literally buckled.

616
00:44:55,800 --> 00:44:57,879
What are you so scared of?

617
00:44:57,880 --> 00:44:59,839
Doesn't she have amnesia?

618
00:44:59,840 --> 00:45:02,359
Even if she's back, she can't hurt anyone.

619
00:45:02,360 --> 00:45:06,399
Do you really believe
Ms. Claire actually has amnesia?

620
00:45:06,400 --> 00:45:08,719
You saw it yourself yesterday.

621
00:45:08,720 --> 00:45:12,639
The moment the reporters pressed her,
she just faked a faint.

622
00:45:12,640 --> 00:45:16,560
She's resourceful.
Do you still think she has amnesia?

623
00:45:19,000 --> 00:45:20,880
<i>How can I help you, Mr. Chris?</i>

624
00:45:21,520 --> 00:45:24,039
I wanted to ask about Claire.

625
00:45:24,040 --> 00:45:28,280
I heard she's in the hospital.
Do you know which one?

626
00:45:29,400 --> 00:45:30,479
I have no idea.

627
00:45:30,480 --> 00:45:34,960
Mr. Chan ordered us not to talk about it,
so nobody knows.

628
00:45:36,480 --> 00:45:38,159
Okay, no problem.

629
00:45:38,160 --> 00:45:39,560
- Thank you.
- Sure.

630
00:45:41,520 --> 00:45:43,360
- Oh, one more thing.
- Yes?

631
00:45:44,080 --> 00:45:45,960
Don't tell Ms. Cha about this.

632
00:45:46,600 --> 00:45:47,640
I won't.

633
00:45:51,040 --> 00:45:53,120
- Don't tell me about what?
- Cha.

634
00:45:56,200 --> 00:45:57,759
- He was...
- I...

635
00:45:57,760 --> 00:45:58,920
I didn't ask you, Chris.

636
00:46:00,560 --> 00:46:01,720
Well?

637
00:46:04,040 --> 00:46:05,239
Uh, what?

638
00:46:05,240 --> 00:46:06,759
You can leave.

639
00:46:06,760 --> 00:46:07,880
Yes.

640
00:46:10,360 --> 00:46:12,960
- Ma'am...
- Leave.

641
00:46:13,600 --> 00:46:14,600
Yes.

642
00:46:22,880 --> 00:46:26,360
Well, I called her in
to ask about Ms. Claire.

643
00:46:28,560 --> 00:46:32,400
I mean... I wanted to know
what the press was reporting.

644
00:46:33,280 --> 00:46:36,120
I didn't want it to affect both of us.

645
00:46:36,720 --> 00:46:39,519
If rumors spread about me and Ms. Claire,

646
00:46:39,520 --> 00:46:42,520
it would upset you, Cha.

647
00:46:46,400 --> 00:46:51,000
You know sex scandals sell best.
I just wanted to make sure.

648
00:46:57,880 --> 00:46:59,120
Yes?

649
00:47:01,360 --> 00:47:02,840
Is the press here?

650
00:47:05,280 --> 00:47:06,240
Good.

651
00:47:09,120 --> 00:47:10,800
Why did you call the press?

652
00:47:16,640 --> 00:47:18,679
That's Mr. Chan. Would you talk to us?

653
00:47:18,680 --> 00:47:20,999
Is it true that Ms. Claire has amnesia?

654
00:47:21,000 --> 00:47:24,439
What happened to her yesterday?
Why did she suddenly pass out?

655
00:47:24,440 --> 00:47:26,359
- What actually happened?
- What's going on?

656
00:47:26,360 --> 00:47:28,319
- Care to comment?
- Can you tell us?

657
00:47:28,320 --> 00:47:31,799
I'm really sorry.
I have an urgent meeting today,

658
00:47:31,800 --> 00:47:33,719
so I can't really talk.

659
00:47:33,720 --> 00:47:37,799
As for Ms. Claire's condition,
I'll schedule a press conference later.

660
00:47:37,800 --> 00:47:40,479
- Excuse me.
- Please answer, Mr. Chan.

661
00:47:40,480 --> 00:47:43,560
I suggest you give them
a clear answer now.

662
00:47:44,240 --> 00:47:48,520
Because leaving it vague like this
isn't good for us or your fiancée.

663
00:47:52,160 --> 00:47:53,839
What? You're confused?

664
00:47:53,840 --> 00:47:59,120
Oh, you're wondering why I'm here
and not in the executive boardroom.

665
00:47:59,920 --> 00:48:00,839
Sorry about that.

666
00:48:00,840 --> 00:48:03,600
If I hadn't leaked that,
you wouldn't have rushed over.

667
00:48:07,640 --> 00:48:10,160
If you wanted me to meet the press,

668
00:48:11,280 --> 00:48:12,999
you could have just told me.

669
00:48:13,000 --> 00:48:15,040
No need to complicate things.

670
00:48:16,480 --> 00:48:19,839
You should stop arguing with me
and answer the reporters.

671
00:48:19,840 --> 00:48:24,119
Right now, everyone is wondering
what really happened to Khaedarun.

672
00:48:24,120 --> 00:48:27,440
How did she survive?
Does she really have amnesia?

673
00:48:29,360 --> 00:48:33,519
Guys, if you have any questions,
you can ask Mr. Chan now.

674
00:48:33,520 --> 00:48:35,160
He's ready to answer.

675
00:49:02,480 --> 00:49:04,999
Ms. Claire's injuries from the accident

676
00:49:05,000 --> 00:49:06,799
<i>have almost 100% healed.</i>

677
00:49:06,800 --> 00:49:08,759
<i>Why did you call an executive meeting?</i>

678
00:49:08,760 --> 00:49:11,959
I just wanted you and Claire
to prove yourselves.

679
00:49:11,960 --> 00:49:14,759
<i>Didn't you tell the press
she's ready to work?</i>

680
00:49:14,760 --> 00:49:18,679
<i>Didn't it occur to you that
if Claire had proof I cheated on you,</i>

681
00:49:18,680 --> 00:49:20,440
she would've used it by now?

682
00:49:21,040 --> 00:49:23,319
<i>Have you heard about
Claire's shellfish allergy?</i>

683
00:49:23,320 --> 00:49:26,519
Chan said you were shocked
when I had the allergic reaction.

684
00:49:26,520 --> 00:49:27,920
Who are you really?
